 People in our area do not really speak
 a dialect. It is more of a lazy speech
 with words running into each other.   
 Here are some examples:               
 I'll atta goo   {I'll have to go      
 Aintcher        {Haven't you}         
 Weryerpurrit    {Where have you put it
 Guitme          {Give it to me}       
 Gizzitear       {Give it here}        
 Tharall         {Is that all}         
 Tarrah          {Goodbye}             
 Luckatum        {Loot at them}        
 Owtelse         {Anything else}       
 Yanna goo       {Are you having a go} 
 Wariya bin      {Where have you been} 
 Gooiy numb      {Going home}          
 Oooya           {Oh dear (oops)}      
 Ooworriwi       {Who was he with}     
 Safto           {This afternoon       
{Words that end with 'y' are, locally, 
{pronounced as soft 'e'.
